<div>
<p><strong>COMPWAN Source Manipulator</strong></p>
<p><strong>Author:</strong> <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/woedenaz" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1404096); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1404096&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1604893093" alt="Woedenaz" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1404096)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/woedenaz" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1404096); return false;">Woedenaz</a></span><br />
All images/styling created by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/woedenaz" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1404096); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1404096&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1604893093" alt="Woedenaz" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1404096)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/woedenaz" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1404096); return false;">Woedenaz</a></span></p>
<p>This is based off my very first SCP ever:</p>
<h1 id="toc0"><span><a href="/scp-2105">SCP-2105</a> - Programmable Occult</span></h1>
<p>Probably best to give it a read if you want to really understand what's going on.</p>
<p>Special thanks to:</p>
<ul>
<li><span class="error-inline"><em>KindlyTurtleClem</em> does not match any existing user name</span></li>
<li><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1604893093" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;">djkaktus</a></span><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span></li>
</ul>
</div>
<hr />
<div id="u-author_block">
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/woedenaz">▸ More by this Author ◂</a></p>
<hr /></div>
<div class="translation_block">
<h1 id="toc1"><span>Translations:</span></h1>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><iframe src="http://interwiki.scpdb.org/?wiki=scp-wiki&amp;lang=en&amp;page=_default:scp-4205" align="" frameborder="" height="" scrolling="" width="" class="" style=""></iframe></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div></div>
<div class="u-faq">
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/component:info-ayers">F.A.Q.</a></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="wan_container"><iframe src="/compwan-source-manipulator/html/b5643221acc3f8891eb6e929c69a55035d89e8a7-1562068551605524550" allowtransparency="true" frameborder="0" class="iframe html-block-iframe"></iframe>
<div class="spacer">
<div class="mask"></div>
</div>
<div class="pretty">
<p>Eight-hour work days five days in a row really grind me down to the thinnest part of my psyche. My coworker, Jen, sits on that bit of psyche and saws away at it with a bone saw made for a blue whale until it just snaps. And today it snapped.</p>
<p>For reasons beyond me, Jen has a crush on me. Every day at work she will not stop speaking to me, flirting with me.</p>
<p>“What are you doing today, Aaron?”</p>
<p>“Do you want to hang out tonight, Aaron?”</p>
<p>“I like your shirt today, Aaron.”</p>
<p>“Have you been working out, Aaron?”</p>
<p>Every time she talks, she ends with this upwards inflection that rings inside me and causes a swift rise of irrational anger.</p>
<p>Her dull blue eyes look at me with just emptiness behind them, waiting for my response&#8230; which is usually just a simple “No.” And after months of her no-so-obvious hints, I decided I'd give her what she wants.</p>
<p>I invited her to my home.</p>
<p>“Hey Jen,” I say.</p>
<p>She quickly turns towards me and smiles, “Hey Aaron.”</p>
<p>“Do you want to hang out at my place tonight?”</p>
<p>She pauses for a second, not nearly as excited as I expect her to be. After so much prodding, I thought for sure she would lose her mind over the offer. But eventually she responds.</p>
<p>“To do what?” She gives me the same empty look she usually does, “Well, I mean, of course. I would love to. Are others going to join us?”</p>
<p>I am perplexed at the question. This is not the response I expected.</p>
<p>“I, uh, found this ritual that's supposed to see who your true love is.” I’m making this up on the fly, she’ll for sure go for it, “It's supposed to work, but I thought you'd like to try it with me.” I force a smile.</p>
<p>“True love?” She blinks before offering the strangest smile, “You know what? Sure! Perhaps we will both find out together.” She gives a lilting laugh before turning back and returning to work.</p>
<p>“Uh…” I stand behind her, in a confused haze, “Right, well, see you tonight.”</p>
<p>And with that, I return to work.</p>
</div>
<div class="spacer">
<div class="mask"></div>
